.container.breadcrumbs
  =link_to "Home", root_path
  %span.arrow >
  =link_to "Services", services_path
  %span.arrow >
  Add a new service

.container.white_bg
  %h2
    Add a new service

  %p.description
    You can add your own services to the service pattern library and tell us what common patterns they use. You can also give us extra details like what steps they include, what type of organisation they sit in or what type of life event they are part of for the user.

  = simple_form_for @service do |f|

    = render 'shared/services/form_fields', service: @service, f: f

    = f.button :submit, "Add this service", class: "button"

